Notes: Saprobic, found especially on wood in both wet and dry habitats. Many species are nematophagous, forming adhesive knobs, nets or ring-like traps in the presence of a food source; perhaps a strategy for life in low-nitrogen environments. Notes: Decay wood, leaf, fruit, seed, soil, fungal material (Põlme et al. 2020); like traps in the presence of a food source; perhaps a strategy for life in low; nitrogen environments. Many species are nematophagous, forming adhesive knobs, nets or ring
